social_posts.post_text: A place we had to stop at twice while in Seattle was Cafe Flora ☕️🍽️ they have a really lovely dining section with natural lighting, a fountain and plants - the ambiance plus the delicious food made for a perfect pit stop before venturing off into the mountains. 🏔️🚗 Also, the fig orange latte was amazing! 🍊😍

@blackbird_foods sent me some pizza and their new wings to try - they are so good! the texture while biting into the wing is probably the most realistic to wings that I can remember. really enjoyed them! have you tried these yet?
While in Washington, my fiancée and I went to @harvestbeat_ and it was a lovely dining experience! the food was amazing 😍
So recently my fiancée made an amazing dinner for us! 🍽️ 😍 “scallops” made from trumpet mushrooms 🍄 and oyster mushroom steaks with homemade chimichurri and broccolini. YUM 🤤

🥕🥦 support small businesses! my friend @aks_plantpantry has a vegan meal prep service that I ordered from - everything is amazing! i’m having some of the soup and praram long song for work lunch today 😍 the pretzel bites are the perfect sweet treat too 🥨 if you’re a mckinney local I highly recommend checking out Alex’s menu! 🤍
lions mane mushroom nuggets 🍄 don’t sleep on mushrooms y’all, they are so versatile and delicious! 🤤

🎄 Vegan pesto breakfast sandwich on toasted french bread with pesto, melted vegan parmesan, 🍋 lemon basil massaged greens 🥬, @beyondmeat breakfast sausages crumbled up with basil and garlic powder 🌿, @justegg with @aks_plantpantry scramble seasoning and pickled jalapeño 🌶️ so damn good 🤤

christmas meal 🎄🤍 @gardein turk’y cutlets with gravy, old bay mashed potatoes 🥔, vegan mac n cheese 🧀 (i used @miyokoscreamery cream cheese + @daiyafoods cheese sauce, unsweetened oat milk for the sauce), lemon basil vinaigrette salad with avocado 🥑 and corn 🌽 not pictured: warm sourdough bread 🍞😍

🌿 Vegan platter with a RAMEN & a PHO burrito! yes, you read that right. Cris and John is a spot specializing in Vietnamese Street Food with a mexican twist and man do they hit the nail on the head. Amazing, flavorful food with vegan options. That lemongrass tofu bao bun was sooo good. 😍 Try this place out if you haven’t yet!
Washington DC eats! 🫶🏼📸🍔

I got the new @beyondmeat steak at @sprouts and it is SO good! love the texture and taste. my fiancée and I have made steak bowls for meal prep, steak quesadillas - so tasty and I can’t wait to use it to make so many different dishes! if you’ve tried it, what are your thoughts? 💭

I don’t know about you, but i’m feelin’ 32….or whatever they said. 😏🥳 thanks for all the birthday wishes yesterday, appreciate the thoughtful messages! i’ll keep it short: I have a lot I want to accomplish this year & beyond, and I thank you for being here and supporting me. much love 💜🫶🏼

🌿As someone who was vegetarian for 1.5 years before I went fully vegan, here are some things that worked for me during my transition to going vegan. I have been vegan for over 5 years now and still stand by these tips! 💯🙏🏼 if you’re a new vegan, working on going vegan, or even just trying to consume less meat and dairy, welcome! 🤗

super functional and awesome gift that my bestie @missxshell got me for my birthday! LOVE the magnetic aspect, makes for a very functional chopping station and I love that you can have multiple knives on the magnetic strip, it’s very strong. 🧲 can’t wait to get to cookin’ 👩‍🍳
vegan jalapeño popper chickpea salad 😋 had this idea in my mind for a few weeks and decided to finally make it. no regrets 😌
D’vegan 😍💯 noodle bowl with veggies, noodles, tofu, and crispy rolls 😛
Vegan steak burrito using @beyondmeat 💯 the sauce I made is hellman’s vegan mayo + @gothamgreens vegan green goddess dressing with some garlic powder. Hope you enjoy! ❤️

Vegan steak bowl, mediterranean inspired ❤️ using @beyondmeat! for the tzatziki I used @culinayogurt plain, lemon juice 🍋, garlic powder, dill, persian cucumber 🥒 I used @spiceworldinc moroccan spice blend for the steak, and paired it with greens 🥬, tomatoes 🍅, onion 🧅 and quinoa and @followyourheart vegan feta. very delicious 🤤 great for meal prep, simply keep your quinoa and steak together to heat up, add your veggies, feta and tzatziki after 🙌🏼 enjoy 😉

dinner last night was 🔥 🧄 🍋 creamy lemon & garlic pasta sauce with massaged kale, red bell pepper, shallot, a side salad and garlic bread. 🥖 I used vegan cream cheese with unsweetened oat milk to make the sauce!
another easy vegan dinner idea 🍴💡 this turned out delicious! 🙌🏼

😍 One of my favorite Go-To microwave meals is @starlitecuisine enchiladas! We don’t always have time to make elaborate meals, but getting in some veggies & making a delicious sauce to drizzle onto the Starlite Cuisine Enchiladas is how I like to elevate it. 🍽️ See the recipes below to incorporate this into your next week night meal that comes together easily and is delicious! ⁣😋
⁣
⁣
📝 Ingredients for Avocado Sauce:⁣
-1 Avocado⁣
-1/4 cup sliced pickled jalapeño⁣
-2 tbsp pickled jalapeño brine⁣
-5 tbsp unsweetened oat milk⁣
-juice of a quarter of a lime⁣
-0.5 oz cilantro⁣
-1/4 tsp garlic powder⁣
🥑 Instructions: Add all ingredients to a blender and blend until smooth. ⁣
⁣
📝 Ingredients for veggie side:⁣
-1 creamer potato, cut into 8 pieces⁣
-quarter of a bulb of garlic, top of bulb sliced/removed for roasting. top with olive oil & cover in foil ⁣
-1/2 red bell pepper, sliced⁣
-6 broccoli florets⁣
-olive oil for roasting the veggies⁣
-salt and pepper to taste⁣
-1/4 tsp: cumin, chili powder, garlic powder. ⁣
-red pepper flakes and cayenne pepper to taste. ⁣
🌶️ Veggie Side Instructions: ⁣
-Heat oven to 400 degrees F⁣
-Cut veggies and garlic per ingredient list, drizzle with olive oil, season, toss to coat. Wrap the garlic bulb in foil once drizzled with some olive oil. ⁣
-Roast the broccoli and shallots for 20-22 minutes, remove and set aside. ⁣
-Roast the red bell pepper and potatoes for 30 minutes. ⁣
-Roast the garlic for a total of 35-40 minutes. Pair with Enchiladas, drizzle with sauce and enjoy!
Spicy Lemongrass noodles with soy protein from @gojicafedallas - sooo good 😍🫶🏼
@northsporemushrooms Blue Oyster Mushroom growing kit has POPPED OFF! 👏🏼 so stoked for these. 😍🍄🫶🏼
vegan buffalo steak quesadilla with garlic chili crunch mayo 🔥 so fire.

🍄 Y’ALL!!! we already have our second flush of several clusters of Blue Oyster Mushrooms from the @northsporemushrooms growing kit! the first round was amazing and I seriously can’t wait for these 😍 the second batch growing now was maybe a week apart from the first. so cool. 🫶🏼✨ #spreadthespore

🥗 sometimes the best meals are the most simple. salad with buffalo chikn and buffalo ranch 😍 for the ranch I used 3 heaping tbsp of vegan mayo, 2/3 tbsp minced garlic, 1 tbsp unsweetened oat milk 🥛, 1/8 cup buffalo sauce, dill, parsley, s&p to taste. hope you enjoy the relaxing vibes. happy wednesday 😌

🧅 I get these packets at whole foods or sprouts. just add to a container of @tofuttibrands sour cream! I ended up adding green onions before serving on memorial day, but I often love adding sautéed onion too. delicious and easy snack for a party. 🎉
🧄🥖 350 degrees, slice your french bread and add butter, garlic powder. bake for about 8 minutes, top with dried basil and parsley. 😘🤌🏼
🍪🥛 made @chocolatecoveredkatie’s cookie recipe last night - super easy and they are delicious! 😍

💥 chili onion crunch pasta 😌 miyokos cream cheese, lemon juice, unsweetened oat milk, chili onion crunch, onion powder, garlic powder, a little bit of starchy pasta water, and salt and pepper for the sauce. heat everything together in a pan and whisk together until combined and smooth. cook your pasta and add it to the sauce, mix until combined, top with sesame seeds, green onion, and some more chili onion crunch! soooo good 🔥
@beyondmeat new chikn patties are gooood 🤌🏼🤤

I was very impressed with @casa.delvegano in Dallas last night. I got the birria enchiladas, soo saucy and amazing 😍 my fiancé got the fried elote pictured second, and then we had to try the churro beignets. We tried other things too and all of it was delicious. I went with my friend @aks_plantpantry, her bf, and my fiancé. good vibes and great food!!! can’t wait to go back, they have a very extensive menu, all vegan. 👏🏻💯🤌🏼 which would you try first?!

🥯 @tofuttibrands sent me an awesome package! here’s all the items that were gifted to me. the delicious poppyseed bagel is locally made, I used Tofutti cream cheese, local farmers market produce and homemade potato chips and homemade pickles. 🥒
buffalo chikn pasta 🥰 definitely a fave 🔥 I recreated the sprouts version a while back and it’s posted in the reel. I did a variation since I was missing some ingredients but still fire as always 😍
it’s a joke, relax. but I really do have an uncanny ability of catching flies mid flight with my hands. 😂
🥗 mixed greens, tomatoes, green onion, crispy fried onion pieces, tortilla strips, v caesar dressing, cilantro. 😋
@thequeenofshebarestaurant Ethiopian cuisine was fantastic. 😍
breakfast sandwich of my dreams 💭 just egg, FYH cheddar, side of chili crunch mayo, breakfast potatoes 🥔, cilantro and tomatoes 🍅
Thai Noodle Wave in McKinney has such great food! Many dishes are easily made vegan and the staff is really nice. Recommend checking them out if you’re ever in the area 🥰
